               <msContents>
                  <summary>Copy of a release from liability for military service on the ground of poor eyesight.  Issued by the prefect Gn. Vergilius Capito</summary>
                  <msItemStruct>
                     <note type="general">Written across the fibers; back blank</note>
                     <note type="general">13 lines; complete except for 2-3 letters at the ends of lines 1-3</note>
                     <note type="general">The hand is in a clear epistolary style</note>
                     <note type="general">Two large holes and quite a few smaller ones; some abrasion</note>
                     <note type="general">Duplicate of P.Oxy. I 39.  Unlike I.39 which has several abbreviations this copy has everything written in full</note>
                     <note type="general">The prefect is referred to as hegemon amphoteron</note>
                     <textLang mainLang="grc">In Greek</textLang>
